Magic, a startup developing a code-generating platform similar to GitHub‚Äôs Copilot, today announced that it raised $23 million in a Series A funding round led by Alphabet‚Äôs CapitalG with participation from Elad Gil, Nat Friedman and Amplify Partners. So what‚Äôs its story?

Magic‚Äôs CEO and co-founder, Eric Steinberger, says that he was inspired by the potential of AI at a young age. In high school, he and his friends wired up the school‚Äôs computers for machine learning algorithm training, an experience that planted the seeds for Steinberger‚Äôs computer science degree and his job at Meta as an AI researcher.

‚ÄúI spent years exploring potential paths to artificial general intelligence, and then large language models (LLMs) were invented,‚Äù Steinberger told TechCrunch in an email interview.
